{
  "answer": "**I was unable to locate any couplet in Mirza Ghalib's *Diwan-e-Ghalib* (mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c) matching the description of \"the heart being a kebab on a skewer\" or similar imagery (e.g., heart/kebab/skewer/spit/roast in English translations).**\n\nThe corpus contains all 239 ghazals in English translation, original Urdu, and transliteration.[^1] Searches for distinctive English phrases like \"heart kebab\", \"kebab skewer\", \"heart skewer\", \"dil kabab\", \"kabab\", \"seekh\", and variations returned no matches in Ghalib's work. \"Kabab\" appears in Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq's *Diwan-e-Zauq* (e.g., \"Sab kababon se namak dil pe siwa lagta hai\" – \"the salt on the heart apart from all kebabs\"),[^2] but nothing equivalent in Ghalib.\n\nIf the couplet uses different wording in the translation or is from another work/author, it may not be indexed that way. The corpus covers classical texts but not every possible interpretation or unattributed verse.\n\n[^1]: *Mirza Ghalib, Diwan-E-Ghalib*, metadata overview via list_works and list_chapters.\n\n[^2]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-E-Zauq*, chapter 7, via search_corpus \"kabab\".",
